						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up at the entrance into the compound of the Kēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1606, Raktākshi • • • • • ba. 10.</hi> It may correspond to 1684 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Much damaged. It seems to refers to some reconsecration of images. It also records the gift of lands made to the gods Kēśava and Chennarāya by some <hi rend="italic">Karaṇams.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
